        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
          "email": "tappro@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-10-18 19:01:49.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
          "email": "tappro@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-10-31 18:50:58.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-2129 llog: protect llog write against concurrent read",
        "message": "LU-2129 llog: protect llog write against concurrent read\n\nllog_write_rec contains case when buffer passed separately from\nheader and tail, resulting 3 writes instead of single one, so\nconcurrent read may read partial record.\nAnother similar case is llog_pad, which writes header and tail\nwith required gap to align records at the end of 8K buffer.\n\nUse dt_read/write locks on llog object to protect writes against\nread. Such '3-writes' case happens only with configs llogs.\n\nSigned-off-by: Mikhail Pershin <tappro@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Idfb94706b2cf8ad22776c1a277b862863f94c2f6\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
